The use of myopic and lazy improvements is a common technique in artificial intelligence, which suggests the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the structure of game trees, which is a topic studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of probabilities and perturbations is a common technique in machine learning, which suggests the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the termination of the process, which is a topic studied in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
